https://leetcode.com/problems/trim-trailing-vowels/description/


class Solution {
public:
    string trimTrailingVowels(string s) {
        while (!s.empty() && string("aeiou").find(s.back()) != string::npos)
            s.pop_back();
        return s;
    }
};


This line checks if the last character of s is a vowel:
string("aeiou").find(s.back()) != string::npos
Breaking it down:

s.back() → gets the last character of the string
string("aeiou").find(...) → searches for that character inside "aeiou"
string::npos → a special constant meaning "not found" (essentially -1)
!= string::npos → means "was found", i.e., the character IS a vowel

